title: Blinken says he will tell Israelis Rafah invasion would be a ‘mistake’
description: Secretary of State Antony, speaking in Cairo ahead of a planned visit to Israel, said he is optimistic a cease-fire deal can be reached.

title: Jews and Muslims in U.S. disagree on Israel’s conduct in Gaza, poll finds
description: A survey by the Pew Research Center published Thursday shows that Americans are split along religious lines over Israel’s conduct in Gaza.

title: Schumer says Netanyahu ‘lost his way.’ Would a new leader change course?
description: Schumer’s argument that new elections, and Netanyahu’s possible ouster, would shift Israel’s approach to Gaza and the peace process may be wishful thinking.

title: U.S. evacuating Americans from Haiti as humanitarian crisis worsens
description: Commercial means for leaving Haiti effectively evaporated this month after gangs attacked the main airport in the crisis-racked Caribbean nation.

title: India arrests Delhi chief minister as crackdown on opposition spreads
description: His supporters say the arrest, in an alleged money-laundering case, has been trumped up by the country’s ruling Bharatiya Janata Party.

title: Mexico, a key U.S. ally on migration, pushes back hard on Texas law
description: Mexico vows it won’t accept migrants deported by Texas under a controversial state law, setting up potential clashes at the border.

title: Would you want to be a communications assistant to the royals right now?
description: Britain’s royal family is facing questions about the status of Catherine, Princess of Wales. Many say the $32,000-plus communications assistant salary isn’t nearly enough.

title: Scientists found an amazingly well-preserved village from 3,000 years ago
description: The Bronze Age settlement at Must Farm, unearthed by University of Cambridge archaeologists in Whittlesey, Peterborough, has been described as a “time capsule.”

title: Nervous Europe explores using profits from Russian assets to arm Ukraine
description: European Union leaders will discuss a proposal to use windfall profits generated by immobilized assets to help Kyiv.

title: Dozens of Rohingya rescued from hull of capsized boat off Indonesia
description: Crammed into overcrowded refugee camps in Bangladesh with dwindling food supplies, many Rohingya are taking boats to Indonesia out of desperation.

title: What to know about Gaza’s police, amid struggle to protect aid deliveries
description: The dwindling of Gaza’s police force has had dire consequences for the humanitarian response to the war: a growing struggle to safeguard aid deliveries.

title: Two years after start of Ukraine war, Russian titanium keeps flowing to West
description: Despite pledges to break economic ties with Russia, the West remains dependent on a Russian metals firm vital to aerospace, raising security concerns

title: Rafah was Gaza’s last refuge. The overcrowded city is now a target.
description: Israel has launched deadly strikes in Rafah and said it will expand operations in the city, where more than 1.4 million Palestinians are already sheltering.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Blinken to visit Israel; U.S. will assess Israeli assurances on weapons use
description: The State Department is reviewing a written assurance from Israel that its use of U.S.-supplied defense equipment does not violate international or U.S. law.

title: Trump’s vague peace plan casts a shadow over Ukraine
description: Donald Trump holds no elected office, but the Republican presidential candidate’s vague Ukraine policy is already being felt in that country.
